cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper presents competitive online algorithms for energy plan selection, which can be viewed as a game between the customer and the energy suppliers. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the online energy plan selection problem and presents algorithms with competitive ratios. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes online algorithms for solving the energy plan selection problem, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses real-world household and energy plan data to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithms, which can be seen as a form of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes algorithms for solving a real-world decision-making problem, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence research.
